    pearls: ["HCM murmur INCREASES with maneuvers that decrease preload (Valsalva, standing, dehydration) and DECREASES with increased preload (squatting, leg elevation) -- opposite of most murmurs","DCM is the most common indication for heart transplant; ischemic etiology is the most common cause overall","In RCM, the key differentiator from constrictive pericarditis is cardiac MRI and biopsy; both present with diastolic dysfunction, elevated JVP, and Kussmaul sign","HCM is the most common genetic cardiovascular disease (1:500) and most common cause of sudden cardiac death in young athletes -- screen with echo if family history or concerning symptoms","Never use digoxin, nitrates, or vasodilators in obstructive HCM -- they worsen LVOT obstruction by reducing preload or afterload","Peripartum cardiomyopathy can recover: about 50% normalize EF within 6 months with GDMT; subsequent pregnancy carries recurrence risk"],
